%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2014%2C%20hundreds%20of%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20staff%20were%20notified%20by%20email%20that%20they%20were%20being%20terminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20days%20later%2C%20the%20EPA%20emailed%20some%20of%20them%20to%20say%20they%20weren't%20being%20fired%20after%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20to%20provide%20notification%20that%20the%20Agency%20is%20rescinding%20your%20termination.%20You%20are%20not%20being%20removed%20from%20EPA%20or%20from%20federal%20civil%20service%20at%20this%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20the%20email%2C%20which%20was%20seen%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20unsigned%20email%20apologized%20%26quot%3Bfor%20this%20inconvenience%26quot%3B%20and%20thanked%20employees%20for%20their%20service.%20It%20also%20informed%20them%20that%20if%20they%20had%20already%20turned%20in%20EPA%20equipment%20like%20laptops%20and%20badges%2C%20their%20supervisors%20would%20help%20them%20get%20those%20items%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20how%20many%20employees%20had%20their%20firings%20rescinded.%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20three.%20All%20requested%20anonymity%20out%20of%20fear%20of%20professional%20reprisal%2C%20but%20their%20identities%20are%20known%20to%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20agency%20employee%20whose%20termination%20was%20rescinded%2C%20a%20water-quality%20inspector%2C%20said%20working%20for%20the%20EPA%20was%20her%20%26quot%3Bdream%20job%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20she%20hoped%20she%20could%20go%20right%20back%20to%20working%20on%20the%20cases%20that%20she%20was%20working%20on%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20said%20she%20wasn't%20even%20sure%20if%20she%20wanted%20to%20come%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20more%20on%20the%20angry%20side%20of%20grief%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20second%20employee%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20ridiculous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20employee%20told%20BI%20they%20were%20in%20a%20group%20chat%20with%20about%20two%20dozen