sider.com%2Fairbus-ceo-boeing-737-max-blowout-makes-very-humble-safety-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGuillaume%20Faury%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20the%20sector%20could%20go%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20a%20duopoly%20to%20a%20potential%20triopoly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20asked%20about%20Comac's%20plans%20to%20increase%20production%20of%20its%20C919%20jet%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20single-aisle%20aircraft%20similar%20to%20the%20best-selling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbus-boeing-better-year-aircraft-deliveries-order-backlog-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAirbus%3C%2Fa%3E%20A320%20family%20and%20Boeing's%20737%20Max.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOther%20aircraft%20manufacturers%20have%20tried%20to%20enter%20into%20this%20very%20competitive%20space%20in%20the%20past%20from%20other%20countries%2C%20not%20necessarily%20successfully%2C%20but%20I%20believe%20Comac%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20succeed%2C%26quot%3B%20Faury%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20to%20its%20%26quot%3Bprivileged%20access%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20Chinese%20market%2C%20which%20he%20said%20accounted%20for%20a%20fifth%20of%20global%20aircraft%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFaury%20added%20that%20this%20will%20also%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20give%20them%20the%20room%26quot%3B%20to%20export%20to%20other%20countries%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20the%20product%20is%20mature.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227904%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Guests%20and%20crew%20members%20pose%20for%20photos%20in%20front%20of%20the%20C919%20aircraft%20at%20a%20welcoming%20ceremony%20on%20the%20tarmac%20of%20Haikou%20Meilan%20International%20Airport%20on%20December%2011%2C%202024%20in%20Haikou%2C%20Hainan%20Province%20of%20China.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b70effeb4be2fff9a5163f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225270%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20ceremony%20for%20a%20Comac%20C919%20operated%20by%20China%20Southern%20last%20December.%3Cp%3ESu%20Bikun%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20to%20do%20a%20certain%20ramp-up%20first%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20current%20supply%20environment%2C%20ramp-up%20is%20not%20an%20easy%20task%20%E2%80%94%20but%20we%20take%20them%20seriously%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Airbus%20CEO%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20consider%20this%20is%20one%20more%20competitor%20in%20this%20space.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20ch-aviation%20shows%20there%20are%2013%20Comac%20C919s%20in%20service%2C%20operated%20by%20Air%20China%2C%20China%20Southern%2C%20and%20China%20Eastern.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20more%20than%201%2C000%20planes%20on%20order%2C%20Comac%20chairman%20He%20Dongfeng%20said%20in%202023%2C%20Chinese%20media%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComac%20has%20also%20held%20discussions%20with%20Saudi%20officials%20and%20Brazil's%20Total%20Linhas%20Aereas%2C%20Reuters%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20C919%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20certified%20by%20regulators%20in%20the%20US%20or%20Europe.%20Comac%20hoped%20to%20win%20EU%20approval%20this%20year%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3EAviation%20Week%20reported%20last%20May%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Airbus%20is%20planning%20to%20increase%20its%20A320-family%20production%20capacity%20in%20China.%20Faury%20said%20the%20planemaker%20hopes%20the%20second%20final%20assembly%20line%20at%20its%20Tianjin%20plant%20will%20come%20online%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirbus%20reported%20a%206%25%20increase%20in%20revenue%20for%202024%20of%2069.2%20billion%20euros%20(%2472.2%20billion).%20Earnings%20per%20share%20rose%2012%25%20to%205.36%20euros%20(%245.60).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIts%20consolidated%20%3C%2Fspan%3Eorder%20book%20%3Cspan%3Evalued%20at%20629%20billion%20euros%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20up%20from%20554%20billion%20euros.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAirbus%20aims%20to%20deliver%20around%20820%20commercial%20aircraft%20in%202025%2C%20up%20by%2054%20from%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShares%20fell%20almost%201%25%20in%20Paris%20but%20have%20gained%2015%25%20over%20the%20past%2012%20months%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20Boeing's%208.5%25%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228996b253-c8e9-489e-a205-c0eae6d13151%5C%22%3EDefense%20and%20space%20woes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20a%20testing%20year%20for%20Airbus'%20defense%20and%20space%20division.%20While%20its%20order%20intake%20was%20a%20record%2016.7%20billion%20euros%2C%20it%20reported%20a%20loss%20of%20566%20million%20euros%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0largely%20due%20to%20a%201.3%20billion%20euro%20charge%20on%20its%20space%20programs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20some%20US%20players%20are%20disrupting%20the%20ecosystem%20and%20going%20at%20scale%20on%20new%20technologies%2C%26quot%3B%20Faury%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20added%20that%20Airbus%20was%20in%20discussions%20with%20Thales%20and%20Leonardo%20about%20consolidating%20the%20European%20space%20sector.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20defense%2C%20Airbus%20also%20took%20a%20charge%20of%20121%20million%20euros%20on%20its%20A400M%20program.%20The%20company%20said%20there%20were%20%26quot%3Buncertainties%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20number%20of%20orders.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbus-ceo-comac-c919-china-rival-boeing-duopoly-aircraft-faury-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740053524000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67b70f366630eb10385d12be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairbus-ceo-comac-c919-china-rival-boeing-duopoly-aircraft-faury-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Airbus%20CEO%20Guillaume%20Faury%20said%20Comac's%20%26quot%3Bprivileged%20access%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20Chinese%20market%