22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-vs-netherlands-differences-in-parenting-according-to-american-mom-2024-5%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Netherlands%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20noticed%20that%20strangers%20would%20intervene%20to%20give%20her%20advice%20or%20help%20watch%20her%20kids.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOverall%2C%20she%20liked%20that%20the%20culture%20was%20more%20focused%20on%20collectively%20raising%20kids.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20first%20enduring%20memories%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraising-my-child-in-netherlands-totally-different-than-united-states-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Netherlands%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20a%20stranger%20asking%20to%20cradle%20my%20baby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonths%20after%20my%20family%20relocated%20from%20Philadelphia%20to%20Maastricht%2C%20a%20small%20Dutch%20city%2C%20we%20went%20out%20to%20eat.%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoms-postpartum-what-they-wish-their-partners-knew-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esix%20weeks%20postpartum%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20having%20my%20second%20child.%20My%20husband%2C%20six-year-old%20son%2C%20newborn%2C%20and%20I%20shared%20a%20communal%20table%20with%20an%20older%20couple%2C%20who%20had%20finished%20their%20meals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%20chatted%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20then%20turned%20to%20us.%20Would%20we%20like%20for%20them%20to%20hold%20our%20baby%20so%20we%20could%20take%20a%20break%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20odd.%20Raising%20my%20first%20infant%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20never%20encountered%20someone%20I'd%20never%20met%20before%20offering%20to%20help%20like%20this.%20Still%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20lean%20into%20a%20new%20culture.%20It%20was%20remembering%20my%20own%20mother%2C%20who%20loved%20kids%20and%20died%20a%20few%20years%20prior.%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20woman%20seems%20just%20like%20her.%26quot%3B%20I%20inherently%20trusted%20this%20woman%20I'd%20never%20met%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20gave%20her%20my%20baby.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20hand%20him%20back%20when%20he%20gets%20fussy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20My%20husband%20and%20I%20ate%20in%20a%20moment%20of%20peace%2C%20with%20our%20son%20staring%20up%20at%20this%20stranger%20lovingly%20holding%20his%20brother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20four%20years%20we%20lived%20in%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20we%20learned%20that%20this%20is%20more%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fculture-shock-the-netherlands-changed-parenting-gift-lesson-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparenting%20norm%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20a%20random%20act%20of%20kindness.%20I%20regularly%20witnessed%20adults%20intervening%20to%20help%20parents%20out%2C%20whether%20by%20watching%20their%20kids%20or%20giving%20tips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20living%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20I%20miss%20this%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurprising-things-moving-to-netherlands-from-us-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDutch%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20helped%20me%20become%20a%20happier%20and%20more%20relaxed%20parent%2C%20and%20my%20kids%20become%20more%20independent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2249585f48-6451-46ee-9491-aea07148ad4a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ERaising%20kids%20is%20a%20collective%20effort%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20was%20recruited%20to%20work%20in%20a%20Dutch%20firm%20in%202016%2C%20I%20was%20nervous%20about%20relocating%20while%20I%20was%20pregnant.%20My%20doctor%20reassured%20me%3A%20I%20couldn't%20pick%20a%20better%20country%20for%20childbirth%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20he%20was%20right.%20The%20Netherlands%20is%20famous%20for%20its%20%26quot%3Bkraamzorg%26quot%3B%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-gave-birth-in-netherlands-postpartum-support-life-changing-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoula%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20parents%20can%20buy%20doula%20packages%20before%2C%20during%2C%20or%20after%20giving%20birth.%20For%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmother-home-births-planned-unplanned-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%20birth%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20eight%20days%20of%20very%20involved%2C%20in-home%20postpartum%20care%2C%20we%20paid%20under%20%242%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoulas%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20not%20only%20care%20for%20the%20baby%20but%20also%20the%20mother%2C%20looking%20out%20for%20medical%20complications%20and%20offering%20guidance%20for%20first-time%20parents.%20They%20also%20find%20small%20ways%20to%20make%20parents%20more%20comfortable.%20Ours%20also%20vacuumed%20our%20house%2C%20walked%20our%20dog%2C%20and%20took%20the%20baby%20so%20I%20could%20shower.%20To%20me%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20privacy%20was%20worth%20getting%20so%20much%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20quickly%20saw%20that%20this%20community-centered%20attitude%20toward%20childcare%20extends%20beyond%20childbirth.%20I%20regularly%20witnessed%20other%20parents%20jumping%20in%20to%20supervise%20kids%20on%20the%20playground%20or%20play%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20they%20would%20chime%20in%20to%20give%20me%20advice.%20When%20I%20rode%20bikes%20with%20my%20older%20son%2C%20I%20learned%20that%20the%20Dutch%20consider%20it%20safest%20to%20stay%20next%20to%20your%20child%2C%20not%20behind%20them%2C%20as%20I%20initially%20did.%20A%20stranger%20taught%20me%20that%20I%20should%20ride%20with%20one%20hand%20on%20my%20child%20to%20teach%20them%20how%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20bike%20lane%20properly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20parent%20in%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20it's%20normal%20to%20accept%20help%20%E2%80%94%20even%20in%20the%20form%20of%20mild%20critique.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22de7e8479-e749-43af-8523-7dd000302f8d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFewer%20screens%20in%20restaurants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20striking%20difference%20I%20noticed%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20is%20how%20kids%20seemed%20to%20be%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etruly%20seen%20as%20members%20of%20society%20%E2%80%94%20and%20were%20accommodated%20as%20such.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20every%20restaurant%20we%20went%20to%2C%20including%20upscale%20ones%20with%20white%20tablecloths%2C%20had%20a%20designated%20corner%20for%20kids%20to%20play%20in.%20It%20can%20include%20toys%20or%20coloring%20books%2C%20and%20sometimes%20adults%20even%20volunteer%20to%20play%20with%20the%20kids.%20It's%20easy%20for%20parents%20to%20watch%20their%20children%20from%20afar%20while%20also%20unwinding%20at%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEverywhere%20we%20went%20understood%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20kids%20have%20lots%20of%20energy%20and%20can't%20sit%20at%20a%20table%20or%20in%20a%20high%20chair%20for%20that%20long.%20Striking%20this%20compromise%20helped%20us%2C%20and%20other%20parents%2C%20bring%20our%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ekids%20to%20public%20spaces%20without%20feeling%20overwhelmed%20by%20tantrums.%20Back%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I'd%20tag-team%20with%20friends%20to%20take%20turns%20walking%20our%20kids%20outside%20when%20they%20inevitably%20needed%20to%20move.%20It%20was%20manageable%2C%20but%20not%20exactly%20relaxing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20American%20parents%20mitigate%20meltdowns%20by%20giving%20their%20kids%20tablets%20or%20phones.%20In%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20I%20saw%20fewer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscreen-free-family-meals-kids-entertainment-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escreens%20at%20restaurants%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20parents%20had%20other%20means%20to%20keep%20their%20kids%20happy.%20It%20was%20nice%20to%20go%20out%20and%20know%20that%20if%20our%20kids%20got%20tired%20of%20sitting%20with%20the%20adults%2C%20they%20could%20go%20color%20and%20play%20with%20other%20kids%20in