nsider.com%2Fmillions-of-millennials-are-caregivers-for-parents-grandparents-2018-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweight%20of%20caregiving%3C%2Fa%3E%20wasn't%20just%20in%20the%20daily%20tasks%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20in%20the%20isolation%2C%20the%20impossible%20expectations%2C%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20consistent%2C%20accessible%20support.%20There%20was%20no%20road%20map%20for%20balancing%20the%20needs%20of%20a%20dying%20parent%20with%20the%20demands%20of%20two%20small%20children.%20I%20was%20fortunate%20in%20many%20ways%20%E2%80%94%20we%20had%20a%20home%20large%20enough%20to%20take%20my%20mother%20in%2C%20and%20I%20wasn't%20yet%20working%20again%20after%20having%20my%20son.%20But%20none%20of%20that%20changed%20the%20fact%20that%20I%20was%20drowning.%20I%20became%20the%20logistical%20manager%2C%20taxi%20service%2C%20home%20health%20aide%2C%20and%20nurse.%20Dual%20caregiving%20was%20constant%2C%20exhausting%2C%20unpaid%20work%20%E2%80%94%20but%20because%20it%20took%20place%20in%20the%20home%2C%20it%20was%20invisible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20died%2C%20I%20carried%20the%20weight%20of%20what%20felt%20like%20my%20dual%20roles'%20failures%20%E2%80%94%20fearing%20not%20only%20that%20I%20had%20fallen%20short%20of%20expectations%20but%20that%20others%20saw%20it%2C%20too.%20Was%20it%20my%20fault%20she%20was%20gone%3F%20Had%20I%20failed%20to%20pay%20enough%20attention%20because%20so%20much%20of%20my%20focus%20was%20divided%20between%20her%20and%20my%20children%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20saw%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-talk-to-kids-about-death-grief-suicide-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildren%20process%20loss%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20own%20way%2C%20and%20I%20learned%20from%20their%20ability%20to%20accept%20fragility.%20It%20gave%20me%20the%20space%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20push%20%E2%80%94%20to%20talk%20to%20them%20about%20the%20circle%20of%20life%2C%20about%20how%20we%20care%20for%20others%2C%20and%20abou